In a saucepan bring sugar and water to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved, and cool syrup. In a blender or food processor pur√©e pineapple with 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons syrup (reserving remaining syrup for another use). Stir in nectar or juice and Champagne. Pineapple mixture may be made 1 day ahead and chilled, covered. Transfer pineapple mixture to a shallow metal baking pan and freeze, stirring and crushing lumps with a fork every hour, until mixture is firm but not frozen hard, about 3 to 4 hours. Granita may be made 2 days ahead and frozen, covered. Just before serving, scrape granita with a fork to lighten texture. Scoop granita into serving bowls.